# Domain(s) come from the SITE_ADDRESS env var (set in env/.env.prod), so adding a
# subdomain or moving to staging is just a config change — no edits to this file.
# Caddy needs every served hostname listed explicitly to fetch its TLS cert, e.g.
#   SITE_ADDRESS=waygon.dev, admin.waygon.dev
# All hostnames proxy to the same Django app; the admin.* subdomain is served at its
# root by Django host routing (config/middleware.py + config/urls_admin.py), so no
# special block is needed here. For local testing use SITE_ADDRESS=localhost (Caddy
# serves it with an internal certificate).
{$SITE_ADDRESS} {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy web:8000
}
